body:
Many generated class destructors have empty function definitions (other than the debug print) in the .cpp files.  We should optimize them away, or at least put them only in the headers.

e.g. recent t_opt_ifjumpgo.v

```
void Vt_0___024unit__03a__03auvm_callback::_ctor_var_reset(Vt_0__Syms* __restrict vlSymsp) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+          Vt_0___024unit__03a__03auvm_callback::_ctor_var_reset\n"); );
    // Body
    (void)vlSymsp;  // Prevent unused variable warning
}

```

